restore_db_file_check(25.10)                      restore_db_file_check(25.10)

Name
       restore_db_file_check

Syntax
        restore_db_file_check {true | false}

       Type: boolean

       Default: true

       By  default, restoreDesign will check all the files inside the saved DB
       directory. If any file is edited, renamed, or deleted,  the  tool  will
       give  an  error.  However, restoreDesign will not perform this check if
       restore_db_file_check is set to false.

